element.name: George's Tree by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

long-description.p:
This area was once the grounds of Portrane House, previously owned by George and Sophia Evans. The architect was Mr Ashlin, a Gothic revival architect,
It's now the home of St. Ita’s psychiatric hospital.Work commenced on the building of the hospital in 1896 and took 6 years to complete. the hospital was built in a revivalist ancient Irish style. In the grounds of the hospital is the George Evans memorial, a round tower memorial built by George’s wife Sophia, following his death.There was originally a bust of George in the alcove of the tower.

The cache is a micro container.
Please take care and rehide the cache to prevent muggles from discovering its location.
